Executive Profile
David M. Sherbin  Chief Compliance Officer, Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary, Delphi Automotive PLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. David M. Sherbin has been an Senior Vice President and Secretary of Delphi Automotive PLC since October 2009, General Counsel since October 3, 2005 and Chief Compliance Officer since January 2006. Mr. Sherbin is responsible for corporate oversight and adherence to corporate standards as well as enforcing formal compliance controls and established processes. He served as Vice President at DPH Holdings Corp. since October 3, 2005. He served as Vice President of Delphi ... Automotive PLC from October 2005 to October 2009. He served as Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary of PulteGroup, Inc. (also known as Pulte Homes, Inc.) from January 2005 to September 2005. He served as Vice President and General Counsel for Old Delphi since October 2005 and Chief Compliance Officer since January 2006. In 1997, he joined Federal-Mogul Holdings Corporation as an Assistant General Counsel. He served as Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary of Federal-Mogul since April 2004, where he was responsible for managing the worldwide legal affairs. Mr. Sherbin served as Vice President and Deputy General Counsel of Federal-Mogul from 2000 to April 19, 2004 and also served as its Corporate Compliance Officer since 2003. In 1992, he joined Heller Financial Inc. as Counsel in the Corporate Finance Group and since 1994, he served as its Senior Counsel for Corporate Affairs. In 1987, he began his legal career as an Associate at the Chicago law firm of Katten Muchin & Zavis. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Logi-Serve, LLC. Mr. Sherbin also serves on the Board of Directors of the Michigan Center for Civic Education. In 1988, he became Midwest General Counsel of the Dukakis for President Committee. He has spoken extensively on corporate governance and securities law issues. He earned his Bachelor of Arts in Political Science and History, with honors, from Oberlin College in 1981 and his J.D. from Cornell University Law School in 1987.Read Full Background




